        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-01-05T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-31T23:30:00-05:00" n="64" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Dhahran advised, on November 15, that “<gloss target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss>–<gloss
                        target="#t_ARAMCO1">ARAMCO</gloss> island marking has been underway since
                    November 3. Islands so far marked include Farsi, Arabi and Harkus. To be marked
                    are at least 20 more. … I believe most of these islands unquestionably in Saudi
                    waters but some lie in disputed areas. Work is proceeding full speed. … In each
                    case reinforced concrete pillar weighing 17 tons set up holding twin brass
                    plates carrying legend composed US under Judge Hudson’s direction. One plate
                    Arabic, other English. … Saudi guards make first landing in every case, <gloss
                        target="#t_ARAMCO1">ARAMCO</gloss> men following to direct manual labor.”
                    (telegram 318, 890.0145/11–1549)</p>
                <p>Jidda reported, on December 29, that markers had been placed on 18 islands,
                    completing the program (despatch 263, 890.0145/12–2949).</p>
            </div>
